x4freetext: Exp.details.
Prelim. group average cross sections (Tables) for
Al, S, Fe, Ni, Cu, ZR, Nb, Pb, Bi, Th, Mo.
Samples were 5 or 3 cm in diam. and 0.4,0.8,1.6,
3.2,6.4 etc. up to 100. cm long. Admixtures less than
Chromium and tungsten taken powdery brazed in steel
thin-walled containers.
Sulphur smelted and poured into pipe, its opened.
For energy up to 4. MeV
For energy more than 4. MeV
Proportional counters SNMO-5 into a moderator
and the water shield diam 2 m, height 2m, with B(4)C
Long counter,fission chamber with  U-235
and integrator of the ionic current were used to
monitor the incident neutron flux.
The target to sample distance was about 1 m,
the target to detector distance was about 2 m.
Functions of transmission was approximated by
sum of exponents. TRNSM(T)=SUM for I from 1 until N
(A(I)*EXP(-SIGMA(I)*T)). Parameters A and SIGMA were
determined from experimental functions TRNSM(T) by
least squares method.
SIGMA Averaged=SUM for I from 1 until 3 (A(I)*SIGMA(I))
D=SUM for I from 1 until 3 (A(I)*SIGMA(I))**2 -(SUM for
I from 1 until 3 A(I)*SIGMA(I))**2. Sufficiently N=3.
Corrections for background, multiple scattering,
energy effectiveness dependence of detector, statistics
were estimated disregardful small and therefore
was not introduced.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Total exp. error contains contribution of
self-screening, dead time effects and treatment error.
Transmissions was measured up to 0.005 five times each.
For each energy the coefficients of approximation A(I)
were determined and given in corresponding tables of
Seminar Proc. 68DUBNA, paper ASS-68/17,1968 together
with their correlation matrix ( see ANALYSIS).
Some errors corrected, REACTION introduced
